---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import { getLangFromUrl, useTranslations } from '../../i18n/utils';

const lang = getLangFromUrl(Astro.url);
const t = useTranslations(lang);
---

<head>
  <title>{t('methodology.title')} — BoycottWithAI</title>
  <meta name="description" content={t('methodology.subtitle')} />
</head>

<Base>
  <section>
    <h1>{t('methodology.title')}</h1>
    <p class="muted">{t('methodology.subtitle')}</p>

    <div class="card" style="margin-top:12px">
      <h3>Current Situation: 2024–2025</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Escalation & civilian harm:</strong> Over 30,000 civilians killed in Gaza (OCHA, 2024), mass displacement in Sudan and Yemen, and record attacks on infrastructure. UN and humanitarian agencies warn of famine and blocked aid corridors.</li>
        <li><strong>Climate breakdown:</strong> 2024 saw record CO₂ emissions and over 40 million climate refugees (IDMC). COP28 failed to deliver binding fossil fuel phase-out.</li>
        <li><strong>Institutional failure:</strong> UN Security Council blocked by vetoes; EU and G7 increase arms exports and military budgets, ignoring calls for ceasefire and humanitarian access.</li>
        <li><strong>What you can do:</strong> Use <a href="/templates/monitoring-sample-en.txt" download>monitoring templates</a> to track local impacts, document evidence, and share with journalists and MPs. Example: log every attack on civilian infrastructure in your city or region, and send monthly reports to local representatives and media.</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="muted">Data sources: OCHA, SIPRI, IDMC, UNHCR, ACLED. See <a href="/en/resources/">resources</a> for templates and guides.</p>
    </div>

    <article class="card" style="margin-top:18px">
      <h3>{t('methodology.analysis')}</h3>
      <p class="muted">{t('methodology.analysis_detail')}</p>
    </article>

    <article class="card" style="margin-top:12px">
      <div class="card" style="margin-top:18px">
        <h3>Real-World Workflow: From Evidence to International Complaint</h3>
        <ol>
          <li>Gather evidence (screenshots, PDFs, public data, testimonies) and store securely (Nextcloud, Proton Drive, OnionShare).</li>
          <li>Verify and cross-check data with public sources and international databases (<a href="https://www.bellingcat.com/resources/how-tos/">Bellingcat</a>, <a href="https://www.lighthousereports.com/">Lighthouse Reports</a>, <a href="https://www.occrp.org/">OCCRP</a>).</li>
          <li>Prepare a clear report or visualization and publish on a public dashboard (<a href="https://datawrapper.de/">Datawrapper</a>, <a href="https://flourish.studio/">Flourish</a>) or send to journalists/NGOs.</li>
          <li>For serious violations, use FIDH/Amnesty templates and file with ECHR, UN, or national authorities (<a href="https://www.fidh.org/">FIDH</a>, <a href="https://www.amnesty.org/">Amnesty</a>).</li>
          <li>Make the case public: the more visible, the harder to cover up. Use media, briefings, social media, and institutional pressure.</li>
        </ol>
        <p class="muted">For safety, see the <a href="/templates/osint-safety-en.txt" download>OSINT Safety Guide</a>. All these resources are used by journalists and activists who have achieved trials, resignations, and law changes in the EU.</p>
      </div>
      <h3>{t('methodology.monitoring')}</h3>
      <p class="muted">{t('methodology.monitoring_detail')}</p>
    </article>

    <article class="card" style="margin-top:12px">
      <h3>{t('osint.title')}</h3>
      <p class="muted">{t('osint.intro')}</p>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://acleddata.com">{t('osint.acled')}</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.gdeltproject.org">{t('osint.gdelt')}</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.bellingcat.com">{t('osint.bellingcat')}</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://liveuamap.com">{t('osint.liveuamap')}</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://earthdata.nasa.gov/firms">{t('osint.nasa')}</a></li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="card" style="margin-top:12px">
      <h3>{t('ai.title')}</h3>
      <p class="muted">{t('ai.intro')}</p>
      <ul>
        <li>LLM-backed narrative analysis and propaganda detection.</li>
        <li>Forecasting and risk-scoring using open data feeds and news APIs.</li>
        <li>Automated summarization for rapid briefings and response planning.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="card" style="margin-top:12px">
      <h3>{t('civic.title')}</h3>
      <p class="muted">{t('civic.intro')}</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Parliamentary vote trackers, SIPRI & arms export monitoring</li>
        <li>Lobbying and funding transparency tools for defense contractors</li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="card" style="margin-top:12px">
      <h3>{t('humanitarian.title')}</h3>
      <p class="muted">{t('humanitarian.intro')}</p>
      <ul>
        <li>UN OCHA, UNHCR datasets for casualties & displacement.</li>
        <li>Humanitarian corridor monitoring and incident trackers.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="card" style="margin-top:12px">
      <h3>{t('methodology.viz')}</h3>
      <p class="muted">{t('methodology.viz_detail')}</p>
    </article>

    <article class="card" style="margin-top:12px">
      <h3>{t('methodology.crowd')}</h3>
      <p class="muted">{t('methodology.crowd_detail')}</p>
    </article>

    <article class="card" style="margin-top:12px">
      <h3>{t('methodology.safety')}</h3>
      <p class="muted">{t('methodology.safety')}</p>
    </article>
    <article class="card" style="margin-top:12px">
      <h3>Quick OSINT starter checklist</h3>
      <ol>
        <li class="muted">Pick a narrow target: company/contract with a clear timeline or transaction ID.</li>
        <li class="muted">Gather 3 primary sources: news, NGO report, or satellite image. Save permalinks and timestamps.</li>
        <li class="muted">Create a one-page briefing using <a href="/templates/briefing-en.txt" download>briefing-en.txt</a>: keep it to one A4 and state the ask.</li>
        <li class="muted">Choose a monitoring template <a href="/templates/monitoring-sample-en.txt" download>monitoring-sample-en.txt</a> and track developments.</li>
        <li class="muted">Run the OSINT safety checklist (<a href="/templates/osint-safety-en.txt" download>osint-safety-en.txt</a>) before publishing any claims or images.</li>
      </ol>
      <p class="muted">Outputs: one brief for journalists, a petition, and a monitoring log. Store logs and replies as evidence in a single shared folder for further escalation.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="card" style="margin-top:12px">
      <h3>{t('methodology.quick_verify_title')}</h3>
      <ol>
        {t('methodology.quick_verify_steps').map(step => (
          <li class="muted">{step}</li>
        ))}
      </ol>
    </article>
    <article class="card" style="margin-top:12px">
      <h3>{t('methodology.osint_starter_title')}</h3>
      <ul>
        {t('methodology.osint_starter_list').map(step => (
          <li class="muted">{step}</li>
        ))}
      </ul>
    </article>
  </section>
  <section style="margin-top:20px">
    <div class="card">
      <h3>Stay informed</h3>
      <p class="muted">Subscribe for regional escalation alerts and rapid briefings.</p>
      <div style="margin-top:10px">
        <a class="button" href="/rss.xml">{t('cta.monitor')}</a>
        <a class="secondary" href={`/${lang}/resources/`}>{t('resources.title')}</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
